<ItacAcademyItem AcademyId="0596" RecordId="021-000008708"><Name>Avvocati (Accademia degli)</Name><City CityId="64"><CityItalianName>Verona</CityItalianName><CityEnglishName>Verona</CityEnglishName><CityLatinName>Veronae</CityLatinName></City><StartDate>1675</StartDate><EndDate>1676</EndDate><DateText>1675-1676</DateText><Notes>For a comment on this Academy, how it was formed, the reasons why it was dismantled, and the list of members, see Michele Maylender, Storia delle Accademie d`Italia, ad vocem. Maylender indicates that manuscript minutes of the meetings can be found in ms 1459 of the Biblioteca Comunale di Verona. See also Corrado Pecorella, `Note per la classificazione della Accademie italiane dei secoli XVI e XVIII`, in Studi Sassaresi, 1, serie 3, pp. 206-231, for a short comment on the activities taking place in the Academy.</Notes><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20843" RecordId="022-000008709"><Name>Tracca,Domenico,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20844" RecordId="022-000008710"><Name>Nicolini,Antonio,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20845" RecordId="022-000008711"><Name>Oliva,Vettor,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20846" RecordId="022-000008712"><Name>Vicipali,Raimondo,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20847" RecordId="022-000008713"><Name>da Lisca,Giovan Battista,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20848" RecordId="022-000008714"><Name>Campagna,Ottavio,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20849" RecordId="022-000008715"><Name>Aleardi,Gasparo,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20850" RecordId="022-000008716"><Name>S